<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO GARY</font><br>
<tt>Mon Dec  8 15:19:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Gary,<br><br>
You hit two of the great realities of war right on the head -- one being the bear days.  Sometimes too tired (weary) to give a damn about what was going to happen next.<br><br>
I take great pride in being a tunnel rat, but feel relieved that I was never in the Ashau Valley.  You guys certainly had a tough AO.<br><br>
I took a three day pass to Vung Tau, but kept putting off R&amp;R.  I never took one.  I was transferred from Alpha to Delta companies when they formed the fourth company.  Alpha Co. was hit afterwards.  I felt awful that I wasn't there.  The second great reality of war.  Funny how it works sometime.<br><br>
Paul.<br>

<p><code>-- pgmahar@nidlink.com  (Paul) </code><p>


